FBIS3-23497 "jptot013__l94025" JPRS-TOT-94-013-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 24 March 1994 LATIN AMERICA MEXICO `Pacifist' Writer Arrested for Killing Candidate Colosio Suspects Identified PA2403050294 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 0359 GMT 24 Mar 94 PA2403050294 Mexico City XEW Television Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Phone interview with Antonio Cano Jimenez, president of the Tijuana Municipal Council of the Institutional Revolutionary Party, by Jacobo Zabludovsky -- live] [Excerpts] Zabludovsky: According to an interview with witnesses at the scene of this event, it seems that one of the suspects, currently under arrest as one of the assailants, worked in a funeral parlor recently in Tijuana. That would indicate that one, or possibly both suspects are residents of Tijuana. [Passage omitted] Mr. Cano, do you know either of the suspects? Cano: No, sir, I do not. Zabludovsky: I will give you the names, which we now have here, in case you have heard of them. Are you from Tijuana? Cano: Yes sir. Zabludovsky: One is Mario Aburto Martinez, who is 23 years old. The other is Vicente Mayoral Valenzuela. Cano: I do not know them. Zabludovsky: He is 45 years old. Cano: I do not know them, Mr. Zabludovsky. [passage omitted]
